––– comment –––
Manticore allows DROP TABLE even with READ lock (intentional behavior per documentation)
READ lock blocks data modifications (INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE) but allows DDL operations (DROP/TRUNCATE)
Rationale: if user explicitly drops table, they don't care about its backup/consistency
See: https://manual.manticoresearch.com/Securing_and_compacting_a_table/Freezing_and_locking_a_table (line 72)
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "LOCK TABLES test_locks READ; DROP TABLE test_locks;"
––– output –––
––– comment –––
Recreate table after DROP
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE TABLE test_locks (id BIGINT, title TEXT); INSERT INTO test_locks VALUES (1, 'test');"
––– output –––
––– comment –––
